components.templateData:
Welcome to Clash Bot!

To handle all of your League of Legends Clash Tournament scheduling needs through discord! The Riot Tournaments are pulled directly from Riot.

Disclaimer

Clash-Bot is not endorsed by Riot Games and does not reflect the views or opinions of Riot Games or anyone officially involved in producing or managing League of Legends. League of Legends and Riot Games are trademarks or registered trademarks of Riot Games, Inc. League of Legends Riot Games, Inc.

How to use Clash Bot?

All of your scheduling will be done on the Teams page. You can navigate to it using the menu at the top left.

Here are a few components and their usage below.

Discord Server Filter For switching between Servers

You can see which Discord Server you are currently using.

If you want to change, just use the filter button to then select any of your selected guilds.

The 'Free Agents' selection at the top can be used as a open Team for anyone across any server to join.

discord

LoL-ClashBotSupport

Discord Server Filter

You can see which Discord Server you are currently using.

If you want to change, just use the filter button to then select any of your selected guilds.

The 'Free Agents' selection at the top can be used as a open Team for anyone across any server to join.

New Team Card

To start, you can create a brand new Team for one of the upcoming Clash Tournaments in the Discord Server you have selected.

Just click on the plus sign and select the Tournament, Day, and Role you want to sign up with.

Team Cards

Each Team contains one of each of the League of Legend's roles.

To assign yourself to a Team for a given role, just click on the role and click yes on the dialog box.

Important!

You can only be assigned to a single Team or Tentative Queue per Tournament.

Tentative Queue

If you uncertain if you will be able to play in a Clash Tournament, have no fear! You can use this component to let your Server mates know you are uncertain.

Click It!
